SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlinale Talents 2027 (Berlin International Film Festiva
 l)
DESCRIPTION:Berlinale Talents is the Berlin International Film Festival's t
 alent-development program: a week of workshops\, the Talents Lab and the T
 alent Project Market during the February 2027 Berlinale\, plus access to t
 he festival's industry network. ELIGIBILITY: international working film pr
 ofessionals with at least 1 feature\, 2 shorts\, or a widely screened or s
 treamed series\, across 15+ disciplines including directing\, sound design
 \, editing\, production\, cinematography and screenwriting. Participation 
 itself is free\; there is a EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early b
 ird before 19 August 2026) and travel and accommodation are not covered. D
 eadline 2 September 2026\, 12:00 CEST. Apply via the Berlinale Talents por
 tal.\n\nOrganisation: Berlinale / Berlin International Film Festival\nLoca
 tion: Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open inter
 nationally.\nAward: Free participation in the week-long professional progr
 am (Summit workshops\, Talents Lab\, Talent Project Market\, industry netw
 orking). NO stipend\; travel and accommodation are self-covered (national 
 film institutes often fund this\; Netherlands-based filmmakers can approac
 h the Netherlands Film Fund). EUR 15 application service fee (EUR 10 early
  bird before 19 August 2026).\nDuration: One week during the Berlinale\, F
 ebruary 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm
 _source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlinale-talents.de/bt/page/c/apply?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany (during the Berlinale\, February 2027)\; open int
 ernationally.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:berlin-senate-arbeitsstipendium-bildende-kunst-2027@artificialnouveau.g
 ithub.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260902
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260903
SUMMARY:Deadline: Berlin Senate: Arbeitsstipendium Bildende Kunst 2027 (Ber
 lin residents only)
DESCRIPTION:The Berlin Senate's work stipends for visual artists fund 8 or 
 12 months of artistic work during 2027 at EUR 2\,000 per month. The progra
 m explicitly covers digital art and media art\, sound art\, artistic film 
 and video (shown in a visual-arts exhibition context) and installation\, a
 longside classical visual-arts disciplines. ELIGIBILITY: professional visu
 al artists who live\, work and are registered in Berlin\; not open to appl
 icants based elsewhere. The application window runs 6 July to 2 September 
 2026\, 11:00 CEST\, via the Senate's online portal.\n\nOrganisation: Berli
 n Senate Department for Culture and Social Cohesion\nLocation: Berlin\, Ge
 rmany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, work and be officiall
 y registered in Berlin.\nAward: EUR 16\,000 (8 months) or EUR 24\,000 (12 
 months)\, paid as EUR 2\,000 per month. No application fee.\nDuration: 8 o
 r 12 months during 2027\n\nMore: https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/fundi
 ng/funding-programmes/visual-arts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.berlin.de/sen/kultur/en/funding/funding-programmes/visual-a
 rts/artikel.230092.en.php?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium
 =referral
LOCATION:Berlin\, Germany. BERLIN RESIDENTS ONLY: applicants must live\, wo
 rk and be officially registered in Berlin.
END:VEVENT
