BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cmc-dmarc-sonic-arts-residency-2026-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260805
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260806
SUMMARY:Deadline: CMC/DMARC Sonic Arts Residency 2026/2027
DESCRIPTION:The Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC) and CMC Irel
 and announce the second year of the Sonic Arts Residency Programme at the 
 University of Limerick Electronic Music Studio for 2026/27. The residency 
 offers Irish and international composers and sound artists an opportunity 
 to develop their creative practice and experiment using UL's facilities. F
 ACILITIES: the Electronic Music Studio (EMS) featuring both digital and an
 alogue workflows\, including a bespoke Buchla 200e\; a 32-channel immersiv
 e sound lab (SpADE)\; a makerspace supporting electronics and fabrication\
 ; and a range of well-equipped recording studios with a wide selection of 
 microphones and production hardware and software. DMARC is based in the Co
 mputer Science and Information Systems Department at UL and has a long his
 tory supporting digital arts\, electronic music\, and computer-aided compo
 sition (hosting the 2022 International Computer Music Conference and 2020 
 International Conference on Live Coding\, the Diffusion Prize with RTE Lyr
 ic FM\, and partnering with Light Moves Festival). PROGRAMME: each residen
 cy lasts 10 working days within one of two windows\, September-December 20
 26 or January-March 2027. Support includes a EUR 1\,000 honorarium from CM
 C\, a travel bursary up to EUR 350\, and an accommodation bursary up to EU
 R 1\,400 (ten nights)\, with DMARC helping identify accommodation. There i
 s an outreach/presentation element: a one-hour talk/performance for the DM
 ARC community of students and researchers\, and required documentation of 
 the process (photo\, video\, recordings\, and/or written reflections) that
  may be published by CMC on social media\; artists may also be invited to 
 contribute to CMC's amplify podcast series or online features at cmc.ie/fe
 atures. The programme runs 2025-27 with support for six artists (4 Irish\,
  2 international). ASSESSMENT: candidates apply via an online form submitt
 ing a CV\, work samples\, an outline of the residency project (including t
 echnical requirements)\, how they propose to engage with the facilities\, 
 and how the residency would benefit their practice. Criteria: artistic qua
 lity of the proposal including development of work using either the SpADE 
 system or Buchla 200e\; how the opportunity supports the candidate's curre
 nt career stage and artistic goals\; demonstrated technical capacity to en
 gage with the facilities\; and balanced representation of genres\, gender\
 , and geographical regions. TO APPLY: complete the online application form
  linked from the opportunity page. Closing date: 11am (IST)\, 5 August 202
 6\; late applications will not be accepted. Questions: jurgen.simpson@ul.i
 e or kfennell@cmc.ie. Applications are jointly assessed by DMARC and the C
 ontemporary Music Centre.\n\nOrganisation: Contemporary Music Centre (CMC)
  & Digital Media and Arts Research Centre (DMARC)\, University of Limerick
 \nLocation: University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).\nAwar
 d: EUR 1\,000 honorarium (from CMC)\, plus a travel bursary up to EUR 350 
 and an accommodation bursary up to EUR 1\,400 (ten nights). No application
  fee.\nDuration: 10 working days\, scheduled within one of two windows: Se
 ptember-December 2026 or January-March 2027. Additional time may be reques
 ted where it does not incur extra cost.\n\nMore: http://cmc.ie/opportuniti
 es/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-20262027?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:http://cmc.ie/opportunities/open-call-cmcdmarc-sonic-arts-residency-202
 62027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:University of Limerick\, Limerick\, Ireland (in person).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:fondazione-prada-film-fund-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260806
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260807
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fondazione Prada Film Fund 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Fondazione Prada Film Fund is an annual EUR 1.5 million fun
 d backing 10 to 12 feature-length films (fiction\, documentary\, and anima
 tion\, 65 minutes or longer) across development\, production\, and post-pr
 oduction. ELIGIBILITY: independent producers and production companies with
  a track record (approximately two or more feature films premiered at majo
 r international festivals) and partial financing already secured\; this is
  aimed at established independent producers\, NOT individual emerging arti
 sts. DEADLINES: 6 August 2026 for projects in production\; 10 September 20
 26 for development and post-production projects (this card uses the earlie
 st deadline). Apply via the Fondazione Prada Film Fund page. NOTE: the fun
 der's primary page was not directly reachable at time of entry\; dates cor
 roborated via industry trade press (Screen\, Cineuropa). Verify the exact 
 track deadline before applying.\n\nOrganisation: Fondazione Prada\nLocatio
 n: Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers and 
 production companies.\nAward: EUR 1.5 million total pool supporting 10 to 
 12 feature films. Development grants EUR 15\,000 to 80\,000\; production g
 rants EUR 30\,000 to 250\,000\; post-production grants EUR 40\,000 to 100\
 ,000. No application fee.\nDuration: Feature film funding (development\, p
 roduction\, or post-production)\n\nMore: https://www.fondazioneprada.org/f
 ilm-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referra
 l
URL:https://www.fondazioneprada.org/film-fund/?lang=en&utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Milan\, Italy-based fund\; open worldwide to independent producers
  and production companies.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-toyful-music-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260715
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260716
SUMMARY:Deadline: Atheras: Nicosia Ludic Lab for Composers\, Toyful Music F
 estival 2026
DESCRIPTION:Atheras Peoples and Cultures invites composers and performer-re
 searchers to apply for the Nicosia Ludic Lab\, a 31-day international resi
 dency dedicated to exploring 'play' as a compositional and performative me
 thodology in contemporary music. Building on the artistic vision of the To
 yful Music Festival\, the residency creates a focused environment where ex
 perimentation\, precision\, and imagination coexist\, redefining how music
  is conceived\, structured\, and performed. The residency runs in Nicosia\
 , Cyprus\, from 23 October to 22 November 2026\, and participants develop 
 new ensemble works that directly shape the artistic programme of the Toyfu
 l Music Festival 2026. ELIGIBILITY: applications are open to individual ar
 tists (proposals from duets or collectives will not be considered) based i
 n a Creative Europe country\, who must demonstrate a strong interest in ex
 perimental\, ensemble-based practices. SELECTED RESIDENTS RECEIVE: full fi
 nancial support (travel\, accommodation\, daily allowance)\; shared accomm
 odation in central Nicosia\; continuous access to a professional ensemble\
 ; mentorship sessions and individual meetings with ensemble members\; coac
 hing sessions with composer and conductor Andys Skordis\; artistic and pro
 fessional guidance from the Atheras team\; rehearsal space and full produc
 tion support for Phase 3\; and video and audio recording of the final live
  concert for documentation and international visibility. Deadline: 15 July
  2026.\n\nOrganisation: Atheras Peoples and Cultures\nLocation: Nicosia\, 
 Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative Europe country\nAw
 ard: Full financial support: travel\, shared accommodation in central Nico
 sia\, and daily allowance. Rehearsal space and full production support pro
 vided\; final live concert recorded (video and audio) for documentation an
 d international visibility.\nDuration: 31-day residency\, 23 October to 22
  November 2026\n\nMore: https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic
 -lab-composers-new-works-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=arti
 ficialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://on-the-move.org/news/atheras-nicosia-ludic-lab-composers-new-wo
 rks-toyful-music-festival-2026-cyprus?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdes
 k&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nicosia\, Cyprus\; open to individual artists based in a Creative 
 Europe country
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ditrapano-finch-manuscript-lab-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: Giancarlo DiTrapano Foundation: The Finch Manuscript Lab 
 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Finch Manuscript Lab is a 2.5-month residency supporting wr
 iters completing book-length manuscripts\, hosted at the Finch Country Hou
 se in Serramezzana\, Italy\, and designed as the final sprint in the marat
 hon of writing a book. It offers living and work space\, writing time in a
  tranquil setting\, creative community\, and professional development incl
 uding manuscript consultations\, craft discussions\, and publishing semina
 rs. Residency dates: 1 October to 15 December 2026\; residents will be sel
 ected by 30 July 2026. FUNDING: thanks to the support of the Goethe Instit
 ute and Culture Moves Europe\, all selected residents receive a stipend of
  EUR 2\,280 for the residency period (EUR 30 per day in residence\, paid w
 eekly)\, a travel allowance of EUR 400 for distances under 5\,000 km from 
 Serramezzana or EUR 800 for distances over 5\,000 km\, an additional EUR 4
 00 for green travel (e.g. taking trains instead of planes)\, and additiona
 l support of EUR 200 for parents of children under 18. ELIGIBILITY: applic
 ants must be over 18 and a legal resident of one of the 39 Culture Moves E
 urope eligible countries\, excluding Italy\; this includes all EU member s
 tates other than Italy and 13 participating non-EU countries (Albania\, An
 dorra\, Armenia\, Bosnia and Herzegovina\, Georgia\, Iceland\, Kosovo\, Mo
 ldova\, Montenegro\, North Macedonia\, Norway\, Serbia\, and Tunisia). APP
 LICATION (via Submittable\, in order of importance): a short sample of pas
 t work (any length\, though only the first 30 pages may be read)\; a brief
  note\, up to one page\, explaining the manuscript or book project to be w
 orked on in residency\, where you are in the creation process\, and why yo
 u are interested\; an excerpt of the book project not exceeding 30 pages (
 prose\, poetry\, mixed media\, photography\, or any other form of artist's
  book is acceptable)\; and a CV in English. NOTE ON DEADLINE: the foundati
 on's text gives the open call as 15 June to 10 July 2026\, while the Submi
 ttable page lists a close of Wednesday 15 July 2026 at 12:00 PM\; apply by
  10 July to be safe.\n\nOrganisation: The Giancarlo DiTrapano Foundation f
 or Literature and the Arts\nLocation: Finch Country House\, Serramezzana\,
  Italy\; open to legal residents of the 39 Culture Moves Europe eligible c
 ountries\, excluding Italy\nAward: EUR 2\,280 stipend for the residency pe
 riod (EUR 30 per day in residence\, paid weekly)\, plus travel allowance o
 f EUR 400 (under 5\,000 km) or EUR 800 (over 5\,000 km)\, an additional EU
 R 400 green-travel top-up (e.g. trains instead of planes)\, and EUR 200 ad
 ditional support for parents of children under 18. Supported by the Goethe
  Institute and Culture Moves Europe.\nDuration: 2.5 months\, 1 October to 
 15 December 2026\n\nMore: https://ditrapanofoundation.submittable.com/subm
 it/171cc54d-b582-47a3-93a4-47c46b65904b/the-finch-manuscript-lab?utm_sourc
 e=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://ditrapanofoundation.submittable.com/submit/171cc54d-b582-47a3-9
 3a4-47c46b65904b/the-finch-manuscript-lab?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Finch Country House\, Serramezzana\, Italy\; open to legal residen
 ts of the 39 Culture Moves Europe eligible countries\, excluding Italy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ramdam-extended-possibilities-residency-2027@artificialnouveau.github.i
 o
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260714
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260715
SUMMARY:Deadline: RAMDAM\, un centre d'art: Extended Possibilities Residenc
 y 2027
DESCRIPTION:Extended Possibilities gives artists the opportunity to work on
  site at RAMDAM\, un centre d'art for 45 days\, a long period allowing the
 m to benefit from technical support and to present ongoing work to the pub
 lic. Artists receive on-site accommodation (a collective room for the whol
 e 45 days)\, access to a well-maintained\, up-to-date technical facility\,
  a grant to support their work\, and a lump-sum allowance for travel and v
 isas. RAMDAM is an activist space supporting artists in their artistic res
 earch\; residencies are open to artists or teams engaged in creation\, res
 earch\, or experimentation\, with no obligation to produce a finished work
 : dance\, theatre\, performance\, painting\, sculpture\, drawing\, film\, 
 video\, literary writing\, screenwriting\, digital art\, and hybrid forms 
 are all welcome. The call focuses on multidisciplinary projects and resear
 ch that break down barriers between disciplines and challenge their own fi
 eld of practice\, and considerable attention is given to how the work fits
  into a social and/or political context and resonates with our times. THE 
 CALL SUPPORTS: 1 or 2 artistic teams (RAMDAM can host at most 5 artists)\;
  performing artists of all disciplines\; projects at early stages of resea
 rch-creation and/or more advanced (residencies can be writing residencies 
 and/or stage residencies). All artists must be available for the full 45 d
 ays from 1 February to 15 March 2027 and must be from eligible countries (
 EU countries\, outermost regions\, overseas countries and territories\, an
 d some non-EU countries)\; artists from mainland (hexagonal) France cannot
  apply. The working and living spaces are wheelchair accessible\, though r
 eaching RAMDAM by public transport can be difficult for disabled people\; 
 accessibility support is available via Culture Moves Europe for residents 
 with disabilities. ALLOWANCES: EUR 1\,350 per resident for subsistence\; t
 ravel allowance EUR 400 under 5\,000 km or EUR 800 from 5\,000 km (travel 
 under 600 km must be by green means of transport unless disability or isla
 nd residence requires otherwise)\; green mobility top-up EUR 400 per resid
 ent for non-plane travel over 600 km\; visa top-up EUR 120\; outermost reg
 ions/OCT top-up EUR 175\; family top-up EUR 200 per child under 18 (housin
 g capacity is limited). TO APPLY: applications in English or French\; down
 load the residency project and administrative form documents and email the
  complete application to contact@ramdamcda.org with subject line 'extended
  possibilities - 2027' (no WeTransfer\, no important information in the em
 ail body\; reduce file sizes\; a third document may be added to help under
 stand the work). Confirmation within 7 working days\; shortlisted applican
 ts have video calls with the residency committee in mid-August. Deadline: 
 Tuesday 14 July 2026\, 11:59 p.m. NOTE: the call is arbitrarily limited to
  the first 40 applications received (still open as of 1 July 2026)\, so ap
 ply early. Made possible by the European programme Culture Moves Europe.\n
 \nOrganisation: RAMDAM\, un centre d'art\nLocation: Sainte-Foy-les-Lyon (n
 ear Lyon)\, France\; open to artists legally resident in Culture Moves Eur
 ope eligible countries (EU member states\, outermost regions\, overseas co
 untries and territories\, and some non-EU countries)\; artists from mainla
 nd (hexagonal) France cannot apply\nAward: EUR 1\,350 per resident allowan
 ce for subsistence and other costs\, plus travel allowance of EUR 400 (und
 er 5\,000 km) or EUR 800 (from 5\,000 km). Top-ups: green mobility EUR 400
  per resident (600 km or more by non-plane transport)\, visa EUR 120\, out
 ermost regions/OCT EUR 175\, family EUR 200 per child under 18. On-site ac
 commodation and technical facilities provided. Supported by Culture Moves 
 Europe.\nDuration: 45 days\, 1 February to 15 March 2027\n\nMore: https://
 ramdamcda.org/actualite-ramdam/extended-possibilities-residency-call?utm_s
 ource=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://ramdamcda.org/actualite-ramdam/extended-possibilities-residency
 -call?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Sainte-Foy-les-Lyon (near Lyon)\, France\; open to artists legally
  resident in Culture Moves Europe eligible countries (EU member states\, o
 utermost regions\, overseas countries and territories\, and some non-EU co
 untries)\; artists from mainland (hexagonal) France cannot apply
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:guardian-arte-democracy-at-stake-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260914
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260915
SUMMARY:Deadline: Democracy at Stake in Europe: Short Documentary Fund
DESCRIPTION:Guardian Documentaries and arte.tv have opened a short document
 ary film fund on the theme 'Democracy at Stake in Europe'\, supporting the
  development and production of a character-led documentary short exploring
  threats\, pressures and challenges facing democratic societies across Eur
 ope. The aim is to amplify personal stories that help audiences understand
  democracy in Europe today and to stimulate public debate\; suggested area
 s of focus include press freedom\, civic trust and democratic participatio
 n. AWARD: one project receives GBP 10\,000 in production support\; alongsi
 de the financial award\, the selected filmmaker receives editorial and cre
 ative input from the partners\, with distribution through Guardian and art
 e.tv platforms. The funding can be used for work linked to the film's deve
 lopment and production\, such as research\, filming and post-production\, 
 subject to the applicant's proposed budget and plan. ELIGIBILITY: open to 
 European filmmakers aged 18 or over\; the call is focused on a single shor
 t documentary and is intended for projects where individual experience and
  perspective are central to telling a wider story about democratic life in
  Europe. Deadline 14 September 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Guardian Documentari
 es and arte.tv\nLocation: Europe.\nAward: GBP 10\,000 in production suppor
 t for one short documentary project\, plus editorial and creative input fr
 om the partners and distribution through Guardian and arte.tv platforms.\n
 Duration: Development and production of a single short documentary.\n\nMor
 e: https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://vibrantshropshire.co.uk/funding/democracy-at-stake-in-europe/?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Europe.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:feminist-gaming-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: Feminist Gaming Fellowship: Open Call 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Feminist Gaming Project is opening applications for its fir
 st Fellowship cohort: five fellows from different creative and research fi
 elds spending three months developing 3D assets\, tools\, and documentatio
 n for its Open Access Asset Library (OAL)\, a free\, open repository of in
 clusive 3D content created by\, with\, and for intersectionally feminist a
 nd diverse communities. Where mainstream marketplaces default to hyper-ath
 letic\, idealized\, or hyper-sexualized characters\, the OAL offers averag
 e bodies\, real postures\, everyday objects\, and the kinds of lives most 
 games leave out (pregnancy and postpartum\, care work\, ageing\, disabilit
 y\, domestic labor). This first cohort is dedicated to 3D content. Support
 ed by the Creative Industries Fund NL and working across the Netherlands\,
  Türkiye\, Germany\, and the UK\, the project challenges exclusionary nor
 ms in how games are made. The fellowship offers a EUR 1\,000 honorarium pe
 r fellow over three months (half at start\, half on completion)\; mentorsh
 ip from the core team and advisors in feminist design\, game studies\, 3D 
 production\, and digital culture\; a peer community across NL\, TR\, DE\, 
 and the UK with biweekly meetings\; visibility through a travelling exhibi
 tion program\, publications\, and public events\; and authorship credited 
 in the OAL under its license terms. Five roles are recruited (one fellow e
 ach): 3D Character Artist for inclusive base meshes\; 3D Character Artist 
 for pregnancy and postpartum assets\; 3D Animator for neutral and everyday
  movement\; 3D Modeller for domestic and care-labor environments\; and Res
 earcher/Writer for documentation and the representation framework\; applic
 ants may rank up to two. Open to 3D artists\, animators\, modellers\, desi
 gners\, researchers\, and writers committed to inclusive and intersectiona
 l representation in games\; prior game-industry experience is not required
 \, and emerging creators\, underrepresented practitioners\, and researcher
 s at the intersection of games\, gender\, and culture are especially encou
 raged\, particularly those based in or connected to NL\, TR\, DE\, or the 
 UK. To apply\, email feministgamingproject@gmail.com with a short statemen
 t (max ~500 words)\, a portfolio or work samples (a link is fine)\, and co
 nfirmation of availability for the three-month period\; name the role(s) i
 n the subject line or statement. The project explicitly asks applicants to
  write statements in their own voice rather than using AI-generated text. 
 Indicative timeline: applications close 12 July 2026\; selection and notif
 ication late July\; fellowship period August to October 2026\; showcase an
 d publication November to December 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Feminist Gaming 
 Project\nLocation: Remote across the Netherlands\, Türkiye\, Germany\, an
 d the UK\nAward: EUR 1\,000 honorarium per fellow (paid half at the start\
 , half on completion)\nDuration: Three months\, August to October 2026\; m
 inimum ~6 hours per week (~75 hours total)\n\nMore: https://feministgaming
 .com/fellowship/index.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_mediu
 m=referral
URL:https://feministgaming.com/fellowship/index.html?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote across the Netherlands\, Türkiye\, Germany\, and the UK
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-expanded-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260709
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260710
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Expanded Orbit 1st Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Expanded Orbit is the first edition of an international 
 training programme dedicated to immersive storytelling and XR-based practi
 ces\, run by the CIRCLE Training Initiative in partnership with Onassis ON
 X. It supports women and gender-expansive filmmakers\, artists\, XR creato
 rs\, and multidisciplinary storytellers working across XR\, MR\, VR\, AR\,
  AI\, and game-based narratives\, with no prior XR experience required. Se
 lected individuals or teams of up to two receive individual mentorship\, g
 roup sessions\, co-creation workshops\, and structured feedback\, plus acc
 ess to an international network of professionals. The in-person training t
 akes place from November 21 to 26\, 2026\, in Athens\, Greece. Applicants 
 should be developing a project with a strong artistic vision and clear int
 erest in immersive formats\, ideally with a producer attached and partial 
 budget secured. A participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per person applies\, wit
 h scholarships of up to 50 percent available based on financial need.\n\nO
 rganisation: CIRCLE Training Initiative (with Onassis ONX)\nLocation: Athe
 ns\, Greece\nAward: No cash stipend. Provides individual mentorship from w
 orld-leading experts\, group sessions\, co-creation workshops\, structured
  feedback\, and access to an international professional network across fil
 m\, art\, design\, and technology. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per per
 son (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\, with scholarships covering up to 50 per
 cent available for those with financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee
  per person (EUR 4\,000 per team of two)\; up to 50 percent scholarships a
 vailable\nDuration: 6 days (in-person training)\n\nMore: https://www.docci
 rcle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=re
 ferral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/expanded-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Athens\, Greece
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:circle-fiction-orbit-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260710
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260711
SUMMARY:Deadline: CIRCLE Fiction Orbit 3rd Edition
DESCRIPTION:CIRCLE Fiction Orbit is a one-week retreat in Herceg Novi\, Mon
 tenegro for up to six fiction feature film projects led by teams of women 
 and gender-expansive filmmakers developing their second\, third\, or fourt
 h narrative feature. Participants work with leading experts on script deve
 lopment\, legal and production strategy\, career positioning\, and receive
  psychological support throughout the creative process. Applicants must id
 entify as a woman or gender-expansive filmmaker\, work as a screenwriter\,
  director\, or producer\, have completed at least one feature\, and submit
  a project with a producer attached. Accommodation and meals are provided\
 , but travel is not covered\, and a participation fee of EUR 2\,000 per pe
 rson applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship is available annually fo
 r those with demonstrated financial need. The third edition runs October 2
 5 to November 1\, 2026\, with applications due July 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: CIRCLE Training Initiative\nLocation: Herceg Novi\, Montenegro\nAwar
 d: Accommodation and meals provided\; in-depth script consultations\, lega
 l and production strategy guidance\, career development mentorship\, and p
 sychological support. Travel not covered. Participation fee of EUR 2\,000 
 per person applies. At least one 50 percent scholarship available annually
  for participants from lower-income countries\, those without national fun
 ding\, or with demonstrated financial need. EUR 2\,000 participation fee (
 accommodation and meals included\; travel not covered)\; 50 percent schola
 rship available for demonstrated need\nDuration: One week\n\nMore: https:/
 /www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_
 medium=referral
URL:https://www.doccircle.me/fiction-orbit?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Herceg Novi\, Montenegro
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prisma-art-prize-20th-edition-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260910
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260911
SUMMARY:Deadline: Prisma Art Prize 20th Edition
DESCRIPTION:The Prisma Art Prize is an international award for painting and
  two-dimensional artistic research based in Rome. The 20th edition selects
  emerging and established artists working in painting\, drawing\, illustra
 tion\, printmaking\, and traditional mixed media for a group exhibition at
  Palazzo Merulana\, opening November 5\, 2026. Winners share an annual cas
 h fund of EUR 2\,000 distributed across quarterly calls and receive inclus
 ion in the collective catalogue plus artist interviews. Additional opportu
 nities include solo exhibition prizes and fully funded placements at partn
 er art residencies. The prize is open internationally to all living artist
 s regardless of age\, gender\, nationality\, or educational background. Th
 e submission deadline for this edition is September 10\, 2026.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Prisma Art Prize\nLocation: Rome\, Italy\nAward: EUR 2\,000 annual c
 ash fund distributed across quarterly winners\, plus group exhibition at P
 alazzo Merulana\, inclusion in the collective catalogue\, artist interview
 s\, and eligibility for solo show prizes (Isorrophia Gallery\, Pallavicini
 -Dettori) and partner art residencies (Dar Meso\, Casacon\, Osservatorioma
 ree) EUR 34 entry fee for 1 to 3 artworks\, plus EUR 5 for each additional
  artwork up to a maximum of 8\nDuration: Group exhibition runs November 5 
 to 8\, 2026\n\nMore: https://www.prismaartprize.com/?utm_source=artificial
 nouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.prismaartprize.com/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&u
 tm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Rome\, Italy
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cmrfe-multispecies-residency-autumn-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260705
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260706
SUMMARY:Deadline: Artist Residency Autumn 2026 (Centre for Multispecies Rel
 ations and Future Ecologies\, Palermo)
DESCRIPTION:The Centre for Multispecies Relations and Future Ecologies invi
 tes applications from two artists for a 62-day residency (12 October - 12 
 December 2026) at its site in the Altarello di Baida district of Palermo\,
  Sicily. The residency is structured around a 1\,500 sqm garden at the thr
 eshold between the city's urban expansion and the historic rural landscape
  of the surrounding hills\; the site\, degraded through previous use (soil
  compaction and significant biodiversity loss)\, functions as both studio 
 and subject\, and artists participate in an ongoing process of ecological 
 transformation\, producing interventions that emerge from extended observa
 tion and fieldwork. Applications are welcome across all mediums and discip
 lines (installation\, sound\, performance\, video\, food art\, participato
 ry practice\, and beyond)\; research-based and interdisciplinary practices
  are especially encouraged. The Centre works at the intersection of art\, 
 science\, and (agro)ecological practices\, with a focus on multispecies co
 existence and climate change in the Mediterranean\, and has been based in 
 Palermo since 2021. PROGRAMME: five phases (orientation with small trips a
 nd gatherings\; observation with independent fieldwork and consultations w
 ith artists\, curators\, scientists\, and anthropologists\; proposal and e
 cological feasibility developed with mentors\; creation\; and public resti
 tution with an open event\, a workshop\, and a public discussion). Each ar
 tist develops an independent site-specific intervention\; the two resident
 s share the site\, living space\, and process\, with exchange encouraged b
 ut not prescribed. Artist duos and artists who want to collaborate are enc
 ouraged to apply (you can apply as an individual for one position\, as a d
 uo for both\, or as two artists collaborating for two positions). Mentorsh
 ip by co-founders/artistic directors Fabio Aranzulla and Luca Cinquemani (
 weekly site visits\, studio discussions\, work-in-progress presentations)\
 ; logistics managed by Francesca Farris. WHO: artists whose work engages w
 ith ecology\, multispecies relations\, or the more-than-human\, who can mo
 ve between observation and making and are interested in dialogue with scie
 ntists\, land workers\, and local communities. Priority is given to artist
 s from working-class and less-privileged backgrounds\, those who self-iden
 tify as part of marginalised communities\, and candidates reflecting diver
 sity in gender\, age\, geographical background\, and ability\; green trave
 l is prioritised as a condition of participation where feasible. Applicant
 s should be open to living and working in a neighbourhood on the margins o
 f Palermo's periphery. Funded by Culture Moves Europe (Creative Europe pro
 gramme of the European Union). APPLICATION: first phase via the online for
 m (opened 10 June)\; shortlisted artists contacted before the end of July\
 ; second phase is video calls with shortlisted candidates\; applications a
 ccepted in English and Italian. Contact: contact.cmrfe@gmail.com. Deadline
  5 July 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Centre for Multispecies Relations and Futur
 e Ecologies\nLocation: Altarello di Baida district\, Palermo\, Sicily\, It
 aly. On-site 62-day residency\, 12 October - 12 December 2026. Open to all
  nationalities\, but applicants must be officially residing in a Creative 
 Europe country (excluding Italy).\nAward: Total allowance of EUR 1\,860 (b
 efore tax) per artist\, plus a travel budget of EUR 400 per artist (for di
 stances under 4\,000 km) with a EUR 400 green-mobility top-up\, plus a pro
 duction budget. Also provided: on-site accommodation in a fully furnished 
 independent house (private bedroom\; shared kitchen\, living room\, two ba
 throoms\; outdoor studio space 100m from the working site)\, access to rec
 ycled/salvaged materials through the Centre's partnerships\, a bicycle per
  resident\, and a final public event.\nDuration: 62-day residency\, 12 Oct
 ober - 12 December 2026\, structured in five phases (orientation\, observa
 tion/fieldwork\, proposal and ecological feasibility\, creation\, and publ
 ic restitution).\n\nMore: https://tally.so/r/81r5Mz?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://tally.so/r/81r5Mz?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
LOCATION:Altarello di Baida district\, Palermo\, Sicily\, Italy. On-site 62
 -day residency\, 12 October - 12 December 2026. Open to all nationalities\
 , but applicants must be officially residing in a Creative Europe country 
 (excluding Italy).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
