 dych during 2027.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:vfa-sonic-connections-open-call-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260719
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260720
SUMMARY:Deadline: Sonic Connections Open Call 2027 (Villa Filanda Antonini)
DESCRIPTION:Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA) launches its Spring Open Call to s
 elect up to 4 artists and professionals for a one-month residency in March
  2027 on the theme 'Sonic Connections'\, focused on experimental music\, s
 ound art\, and performances. Hosted at Villa Filanda Antonini\, a former s
 ilk mill in Villorba\, Italy\, the project brings together four internatio
 nal artists and professionals to examine the relationship between architec
 ture\, landscape\, and collective sonic experience. ADDRESSED TO: artists\
 , performers\, curators\, designers\, and professionals not currently resi
 ding in Italy. GRANT & BENEFITS: a fully funded residency covering mentori
 ng\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily salary\
 , plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend. WHEN: 1-31 March 2027. HOW TO APPLY
 : complete the application form and attach a CV\, portfolio\, project prop
 osal\, and letter of reference. The VFA residency program has been selecte
 d under conditions by Culture Moves Europe\, a project funded by the Europ
 ean Union and implemented by the Goethe-Institut. Deadline: 19 July 2026\,
  23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Villa Filanda Antonini (VFA)\nLocation: Vill
 orba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and professionals 
 NOT currently residing in Italy.\nAward: Fully funded residency covering m
 entoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily s
 alary\, plus a EUR 1\,000 residency stipend.\nDuration: One-month residenc
 y\, 1-31 March 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections
 -open-call-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections-open-call-2027/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Villorba\, Italy (a former silk mill). Addressed to artists and pr
 ofessionals NOT currently residing in Italy.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ddc-trygfonden-fellowship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Digital Democracy Centre x TrygFonden Fellowship Program 
 2027
DESCRIPTION:The Digital Democracy Centre (DDC) at the University of Souther
 n Denmark\, with support from TrygFonden\, is calling for applications for
  its 2027 fellowship cohort. The program fosters collaboration between res
 earchers\, journalists\, and policymakers exploring the impact of digital 
 technology and AI on media\, politics\, and democracy. Fellows collaborate
  with a self-selected DDC mentor to generate new knowledge\, contribute to
  public debate\, develop networks\, and produce tangible outreach outputs 
 such as policy briefs\, educational packages\, and talks. THREE FELLOWSHIP
  TYPES: (1) academic fellows researching digital technologies and democrac
 y\; (2) journalist fellows covering digital technology and democracy\; (3)
  policy fellows contributing to the regulatory debate. Target group: resea
 rchers\, journalism graduates\, and policymakers in research/educational i
 nstitutions\, media organizations\, ministries\, NGOs\, etc. PRIORITIES: p
 rojects with clear relevance to Denmark or Danish society (including compa
 rative/international projects yielding insights relevant to a Danish conte
 xt)\; in 2027\, projects related to DDC's Hybrid Warfare Initiative (socie
 tal resilience to new forms of international conflict\, with a focus on di
 gital technologies and AI) are also prioritized. EXPECTATIONS: applicants 
 must secure confirmation of mentorship from their desired DDC mentor BEFOR
 E applying (applications without a confirmed mentor are automatically reje
 cted\; PhD students and research assistants are generally not eligible as 
 mentors\, and Sten Schaumburg-Muller is unavailable as a mentor for the 20
 27 call)\; applicants must also coordinate support from their current supe
 rvisors/managers. Fellows engage in DDC activities\, seminars/workshops\, 
 and public outreach\, and submit a short report within two months of finis
 hing. APPLICATION (in English): preliminary project title\, fellowship typ
 e\, brief project description (max 1000 chars)\, detailed description and 
 timeline (max 2400 chars\, including duration\, confirmed mentor\, and rem
 ote/in-office work plan)\, description of activities and collaboration wit
 h external practice partners (max 1000 chars)\, expected product/impact/ou
 tput (max 500 chars)\, a CV (max 5 pages)\, and an overview of the posts f
 or which financial support is sought. Submit the application form (PDF or 
 Word) plus CV as PDFs to ddc@sdu.dk with subject line 'DDC / TrygFonden Fe
 llowship application'. Deadline 1 September 2026\; decisions communicated 
 no later than 1 October 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Digital Democracy Centre (U
 niversity of Southern Denmark)\, with support from TrygFonden\nLocation: O
 dense\, Denmark (University of Southern Denmark). Flexible mix of in-offic
 e stays at the DDC in Odense and remote periods\; stays planned to the Dan
 ish working calendar.\nAward: Either a salary subsidy or a stipend to help
  with travel and/or housing\; specific benefits (financial support\, acces
 s to DDC research resources\, flexible working spaces\, speaker series\, n
 etworks) vary by agreement between the fellow\, DDC\, and partnering organ
 izations. Applicants describe the posts they seek support for (flights\, h
 ousing\, research costs\, salary compensation\, stipend\, etc.).\nDuration
 : Flexible\; typically 2-6 months (minimum two months\, can include shorte
 r DDC stays and remote periods)\, longer in exceptional cases. Fellowships
  start anywhere in 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.sdu.dk/en/forskning/forsknin
 gsenheder/samf/digitaldemocracycentre/news+folder/ddcxtrygfonden-fellowshi
 p-call-2027?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.sdu.dk/en/forskning/forskningsenheder/samf/digitaldemocracy
 centre/news+folder/ddcxtrygfonden-fellowship-call-2027?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Odense\, Denmark (University of Southern Denmark). Flexible mix of
  in-office stays at the DDC in Odense and remote periods\; stays planned t
 o the Danish working calendar.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:manuel-antonio-da-mota-prize-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Deadline: Manuel António da Mota Prize – 17th Edition (2026)
DESCRIPTION:In its 17th edition in 2026\, under the motto 'Always in Solida
 rity\,' the Manuel António da Mota Prize recognizes institutions that exc
 el in the fight against poverty and social exclusion\; the reception and i
 ntegration of migrants and refugees\; the development of rural areas and t
 erritorial cohesion\; health\; education\; employment\; family support\; i
 nnovation and social entrepreneurship\; inclusion and digital and technolo
 gical transition\; and climate transition. AWARDS: the winning application
  receives a cash prize of EUR 50\,000\; second and third place receive EUR
  25\,000 and EUR 10\,000 respectively\; the remaining seven applications (
 honourable mentions) each receive EUR 5\,000. The prize is run by the Fund
 ação Manuel António da Mota. Applications are open until 30 June 2026. 
 See the foundation's current-edition page for full rules and eligibility.\
 n\nOrganisation: Fundação Manuel António da Mota (FMAM)\nLocation: Port
 ugal. Open to private social solidarity institutions and other non-profit 
 entities working in eligible areas.\nAward: Total prize fund. The winning 
 application receives a cash prize of EUR 50\,000. Second and third place r
 eceive EUR 25\,000 and EUR 10\,000 respectively. The remaining 7 applicati
 ons (honourable mentions) each receive a cash prize of EUR 5\,000.\nDurati
 on: One-off award.\n\nMore: https://www.fmam.pt/edicao-em-curso-introducao
 /?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.fmam.pt/edicao-em-curso-introducao/?utm_source=artificialno
 uveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Portugal. Open to private social solidarity institutions and other
  non-profit entities working in eligible areas.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ay-roop-le-milieu-reuse-circus-residency-2026@artificialnouveau.github.
 io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260703
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260704
SUMMARY:Deadline: AY-ROOP / Le Milieu: Reuse - (Re)making for Circus Reside
 ncy 2026 (Rennes Métropole\, France)
DESCRIPTION:AY-ROOP is launching an open call to select three circus artist
 s and/or circus set designers/builders for a 21-day Culture Moves Europe r
 esearch residency at Le Milieu (Saint-Jacques-de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métrop
 ole) from 28 November to 18 December 2026. The residency is a research lab
 oratory on reuse in contemporary circus: how everyday\, locally available 
 materials (paper/cardboard\, plastics\, lightweight metal\, textiles\, rec
 laimed wood\, bicycle parts\, etc.) can be used to create scenographic ele
 ments\, sets\, props and small apparatuses for juggling\, acrobatics and b
 alancing. The core principle is that objects are recreated locally from re
 sources available in each territory rather than transported. AY-ROOP provi
 des an equipped construction workshop\, a rehearsal stage and circus tent\
 , a guide to local reuse-sector contacts\, and a full residency environmen
 t (accommodation\, shared kitchen\, working facilities)\; two mentors (a r
 euse specialist and a performing-arts professional) support the artists. P
 ROFILES: circus artists interested in construction/scenography/DIY making\
 , and builders/set designers working in circus\; individual or group appli
 cations (max 3 people per group)\; emerging or established\, any backgroun
 d. Accessible to artists with disabilities and accessibility needs. Workin
 g language English. No aerial apparatus or rigging: all work is ground-bas
 ed. ELIGIBILITY: aged 18+ (no upper limit)\; legally resident in a Creativ
 e Europe country other than France and DROM-COM\; available for the full r
 esidency. APPLY with a single PDF (1-page bio/CV\, 5-page portfolio or vid
 eo links\, 1-page statement of intent\, proof of residence). DEADLINE: 3 J
 uly 2026. Results announced 13 July 2026. Check the linked call PDF for fu
 ll details.\n\nOrganisation: AY-ROOP\nLocation: Le Milieu\, Saint-Jacques-
 de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métropole\, France. Applicants must legally reside i
 n a Creative Europe country other than France and the French overseas terr
 itories (DROM-COM).\nAward: Funded through Culture Moves Europe: EUR 900 m
 obility allowance per person plus flat-rate travel coverage\; supplements 
 for green mobility\, visa fees\, dependent children under 18\, OCT/OR resi
 dents\, and disability/accessibility needs (including possible full covera
 ge of a sign-language interpreter). On-site single-room accommodation\, lu
 nches at Le Milieu canteen (Tuesday to Friday)\, shared kitchen\, and tech
 nical support provided. No application fee.\nDuration: 21-day residency\, 
 28 November to 18 December 2026.\n\nMore: https://circusdance.fi/ilmoituks
 et/ay-roop-le-milieu-rennes-metropole-france-open-call-for-circus-artists-
 and-set-designers-for-a-residency-focused-on-the-reuse-of-materials-nov-de
 c-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://circusdance.fi/ilmoitukset/ay-roop-le-milieu-rennes-metropole-f
 rance-open-call-for-circus-artists-and-set-designers-for-a-residency-focus
 ed-on-the-reuse-of-materials-nov-dec-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Le Milieu\, Saint-Jacques-de-la-Lande\, Rennes Métropole\, France
 . Applicants must legally reside in a Creative Europe country other than F
 rance and the French overseas territories (DROM-COM).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:musikfonds-stip-6-ai-scholarship-2027@artificialnouveau.github.io
