UID:music-worx-incubator-hamburg-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260617
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260618
SUMMARY:Deadline: Music WorX: Music-Tech Incubator 2026 (Hamburg)
DESCRIPTION:Music WorX is the music-technology incubator run by Hamburg Kre
 ativ Gesellschaft for early-stage teams building products at the intersect
 ion of music and technology (creation tools\, interactive media\, streamin
 g and monetisation\, AI for music\, instruments and audio gear). Selected 
 teams receive a EUR 3\,200 development budget for support services plus a 
 EUR 1\,500 per month living allowance over the 3-month programme\, mentori
 ng from a European music-tech network\, and the chance to win a EUR 1\,000
  audience prize and a EUR 2\,500 jury prize at demo day. The incubator tak
 es no equity. Open to European founders and founding teams (teams of at le
 ast two recommended\, solo founders welcome)\; no formal company formation
  is required to apply. The programme runs roughly September to December 20
 26. Application deadline: 17 June 2026. Apply via the Airtable form linked
  from the official programme page.\n\nOrganisation: Hamburg Kreativ Gesell
 schaft (Kreativ Gesellschaft)\nLocation: Hamburg\, Germany. Open to Europe
 an founders and founding teams\; Hamburg-anchored program with a European 
 mentor network.\nAward: EUR 3\,200 development budget per team plus a EUR 
 1\,500 per month living allowance across the 3-month programme. End-of-pro
 gramme prizes: EUR 1\,000 audience award and EUR 2\,500 jury award. No equ
 ity is taken. No application fee.\nDuration: 3-month programme\, roughly e
 arly September to early December 2026.\n\nMore: https://kreativgesellschaf
 t.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/music-worx/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://kreativgesellschaft.org/en/innovation-inkubatoren/inkubatoren/m
 usic-worx/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hamburg\, Germany. Open to European founders and founding teams\; 
 Hamburg-anchored program with a European mentor network.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eic-accelerator-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260708
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260709
SUMMARY:Deadline: EIC Accelerator 2026 (European Innovation Council)
DESCRIPTION:The EIC Accelerator funds high-risk\, high-impact deep-tech SME
 s and start-ups to develop and scale breakthrough innovations. It offers a
  grant of up to EUR 2.5 million (a non-dilutive lump sum) for innovation a
 ctivities\, and can combine this with an equity investment of EUR 1-10 mil
 lion through the EIC Fund (blended finance)\, or provide investment only. 
 The Step 1 short application can be submitted at any time\; full (Step 2) 
 applications are evaluated at fixed cut-offs. The next 2026 cut-offs are 8
  July\, 2 September and 4 November 2026 (all 17:00 Brussels time). Eligibl
 e applicants are for-profit SMEs and start-ups (fewer than 250 employees\,
  turnover up to EUR 50M or balance sheet up to EUR 43M) established in an 
 EU Member State or Horizon Europe Associated Country\; small mid-caps up t
 o 499 employees are eligible for investment-only support. Apply via the EU
  Funding and Tenders portal (topic HORIZON-EIC-2026-ACCELERATOR-01).\n\nOr
 ganisation: European Innovation Council (European Commission)\nLocation: E
 U Member States and Horizon Europe Associated Countries. Single-company ap
 plicants\; third-country applicants must relocate before the full-applicat
 ion stage.\nAward: Grant up to EUR 2.5 million (non-dilutive lump sum) for
  innovation activities\, plus optional equity investment of EUR 1-10 milli
 on via the EIC Fund. Options: grant-only\, blended finance\, or investment
 -only. No application fee.\nDuration: Project-based\; supports development
  and scale-up at TRL 5/6 to 8.\n\nMore: https://eic.ec.europa.eu/eic-fundi
 ng-opportunities/eic-accelerator_en?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral
URL:https://eic.ec.europa.eu/eic-funding-opportunities/eic-accelerator_en?u
 tm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:EU Member States and Horizon Europe Associated Countries. Single-c
 ompany applicants\; third-country applicants must relocate before the full
 -application stage.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:eurostars-call-11-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260910
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260911
SUMMARY:Deadline: Eurostars Call 11 2026 (Eureka / Eurostars-3)
DESCRIPTION:Eurostars (part of the Eureka network\, the Eurostars-3 program
 me co-funded by Horizon Europe) supports collaborative international R&D p
 rojects led by innovative SMEs. Each country funds its own participants\, 
 so amounts vary\; for the Dutch share\, RVO funds up to EUR 500\,000 per p
 roject at a 50 percent reimbursement rate on eligible R&D costs. Projects 
 require an international consortium of at least two independent organisati
 ons from at least two Eurostars countries\, led by an innovative SME\, wit
 h the SME budget at least 50 percent of the total and no single participan
 t exceeding 70 percent. Projects must run no longer than 36 months and be 
 civil (non-defence) in purpose. Call 11 opens 9 July 2026 and closes 10 Se
 ptember 2026\, 14:00 CEST. No application fee. Submit via the Eureka proje
 ct platform (myeurekaproject.org)\; Dutch national information at RVO.\n\n
 Organisation: Eureka / Eurostars-3 (Dutch participation via RVO)\nLocation
 : International consortia from at least two Eurostars countries\, led by a
 n innovative SME. Dutch funding administered by RVO.\nAward: Co-funds coll
 aborative international R&D\; national funding varies by country. For the 
 Dutch project share: up to EUR 500\,000 per project at 50 percent reimburs
 ement of eligible R&D costs. No application fee.\nDuration: Projects up to
  36 months.\n\nMore: https://www.eurekanetwork.org/programmes-and-calls/eu
 rostars/eurostars-call-for-projects-september-2026/?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.eurekanetwork.org/programmes-and-calls/eurostars/eurostars-
 call-for-projects-september-2026/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&ut
 m_medium=referral
LOCATION:International consortia from at least two Eurostars countries\, le
 d by an innovative SME. Dutch funding administered by RVO.
END:VEVENT
