DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260704
SUMMARY:Deadline: Hubert Butler Essay Prize 2026
DESCRIPTION:Annual essay prize for a previously unpublished essay of up to 
 3\,000 words on a set theme. The 2026 theme takes Auden's line 'Poetry mak
 es nothing happen' as a prompt about what impact high culture can have in 
 a world facing crisis - well suited to a critical essayist working on AI\,
  media and society. Judged blind\, so it is open to and fair for debut wri
 ters (no publication history required). ELIGIBILITY: entrants must be over
  18 and a citizen of the UK or an EU member state. Deadline 3 July 2026.\n
 \nOrganisation: Hubert Butler Essay Prize (with Haus Publishing)\nLocation
