UID:simone-veil-prize-jewish-cultural-heritage-2026@artificialnouveau.githu
 b.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T204113Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260801
SUMMARY:Deadline: Simone Veil Prize for European Jewish Cultural Heritage 2
 026
DESCRIPTION:The Simone Veil Prize\, administered by the European Commission
 \, recognises outstanding projects preserving and promoting European Jewis
 h cultural heritage. It is awarded across five categories: Shared Historie
 s\, Heritage for Dialogue\, Living Heritage\, Cross-border Cooperation and
  Shared Narratives\, and Next Generation/Youth Engagement and Education. A
 WARD: €10\,000 per Grand Prix winner (one per category\, five in total)\
 ; up to 25 finalists receive recognition. ELIGIBILITY: legal or natural pe
 rsons (individuals or organisations) registered in EU Member States or thi
 rd countries associated to the Creative Europe programme\; projects must h
 ave been completed between January 2023 and January 2026. DEADLINE: 31 Jul
 y 2026 at 23:59 CET. APPLY by submitting the completed application form by
  email to applications@simoneveilprize.eu.\n\nOrganisation: European Commi
 ssion\, Directorate-General for Education\, Youth\, Sport and Culture\nLoc
 ation: EU Member States and third countries associated to the Creative Eur
 ope programme\nAward: €10\,000 per Grand Prix winner (five winners\, one
  per category)\; up to 25 finalists recognized. No application fee.\nDurat
 ion: For projects completed between January 2023 and January 2026\n\nMore:
  https://simoneveilprize.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_med
 ium=referral
URL:https://simoneveilprize.eu/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_m
 edium=referral
LOCATION:EU Member States and third countries associated to the Creative Eu
 rope programme
END:VEVENT
