SUMMARY:Deadline: Villa Filanda Antonini: "Sonic Connections" Open Call 202
 7
DESCRIPTION:Villa Filanda Antonini launches its Spring Open Call to select 
 up to four artists and professionals for a one-month residency in March 20
 27\, focused on the theme "Sonic Connections." Hosted at Villa Filanda Ant
 onini\, a former silk mill in Villorba\, Italy\, the residency centres on 
 experimental music\, sound art\, and performance\, bringing together four 
 international artists and professionals to examine the relationship betwee
 n architecture\, landscape\, and collective sonic experience. ADDRESSED TO
 : sound artists\, performers\, curators\, professionals\, and designers wh
 o have completed their studies and reside in Europe (excluding Italy) and 
 in OCTs/ORs countries. GRANT & BENEFITS: fully funded residency covering m
 entoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, production costs\, and a daily s
 alary. WHEN: 1 March to 31 March 2027. HOW TO APPLY: complete the applicat
 ion form and attach your CV\, portfolio\, project proposal\, and a letter 
 of reference. DEADLINE: 19 July 2026\, 23:59 CEST.\n\nOrganisation: Villa 
 Filanda Antonini\nLocation: Villorba (Treviso)\, Italy.\nAward: Fully fund
 ed residency covering mentoring\, accommodation\, travel costs\, productio
 n costs\, and a daily salary. No application fee.\nDuration: One-month res
 idency\, 1-31 March 2027.\n\nMore: https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connec
 tions-open-call-2027/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=ref
 erral
URL:https://www.vfa.art/events/sonic-connections-open-call-2027/?utm_source
 =artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Villorba (Treviso)\, Italy.
END:VEVENT
