SUMMARY:Deadline: Arts Council of Ireland: Visual Arts Project Award 2027
DESCRIPTION:The Arts Council of Ireland's Visual Arts Project Award funds p
 rofessional visual artists\, curators\, and producers to develop and deliv
 er visual arts projects\, in three strands: planning and pre-production (u
 p to EUR 12\,000)\, production and engagement (up to EUR 60\,000)\, and pa
 rtnership production (up to EUR 150\,000). Primarily aimed at applicants b
 ased in the Republic of Ireland\, but the Arts Council's standard eligibil
 ity clause allows applicants based elsewhere where the application explici
 tly demonstrates how the outcomes will benefit the arts in Ireland. The wi
 der Project Award 2027 covers nine disciplines including film and music on
  a similar timeline. Deadline 23 July 2026\, 17:30 Irish time.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Arts Council of Ireland / An Chomhairle Ealaion\nLocation: Republic 
 of Ireland. Applicants based outside Ireland may apply if the application 
 clearly shows how outcomes benefit the arts in the Republic of Ireland.\nA
 ward: Three strands: up to EUR 12\,000 (planning and pre-production)\, up 
 to EUR 60\,000 (production and engagement)\, up to EUR 150\,000 (partnersh
 ip production). No application fee.\nDuration: Projects delivered in 2027.
 \n\nMore: https://artscouncil.ie/funding-opportunities/project-award/visua
 l-arts-project-award/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=ref
 erral
